@NODE About  "Neptune Documentation - About the program"
@TOC Main


   @{b}@{i}Current version@{ui}@{ub} is @{fg shine}1.0@{fg text}


   @{fg shine}Neptune@{fg text} is @{i}shareware@{ui}: this means that
 the @{fg fill}@{b}demo version@{ub}@{fg text} can be freely distributed
 as long as you don't ask any more money for it than a nominal fee for
 copying. If you want to distribute the demo you must mantain the integrity
 of its @{"archive" LINK Overview}. The demo cannot be used for commercial
 purposes without a written permission of the @{"author" LINK Author}.


   The @{"registered version" LINK Registering}, which will contain the registered
 user's @{b}name@{ub} and @{b}address@{ub}, cannot obviously be distributed.


   Neptune was written in @{"MaxonBASIC3" LINK Maxon}.


   None of the files of the Neptune package may be modified. Crunching or
 archiving is allowed only if none of the Neptune files gets modified by it.


@ENDNODE

