@NODE Usage "Neptune Documentation - Usage"
@TOC Main


   @{b}Usage@{ub}


   After doubleclicking on its icon, @{i}@{fg shine}Neptune@{fg text}@{ui}
 will start loading. In some moments (depending on the speed of your
 system) you will be able to select one of the following options from the
 menus:


   @{"Project " LINK Project}

   @{"Display " LINK Display}

   @{"Transits" LINK Transits}

   @{"Print   " LINK Print}

   @{"Animate " LINK Animate}


   @{fg fill}NOTE:@{fg text}

   Some menus can be ghosted because data entry is needed first, or because unavailable in the demo or in the actual version.


   @{b}Other features@{ub}:


   @{"Online Help" LINK Help}

   @{"Windows    " LINK Windows}

@ENDNODE

@node Help "Usage - Online Help"
@TOC Usage


   @{b}Online Help@{ub}


   By @{i}single-clicking@{ui} on a @{b}planet@{ub} or a @{b}sign@{ub} in
 the @{"Graphics Output Window" LINK GfxWin}, its name will be displayed
 until a further single-click on the background.

   By pressing the @{i}Help@{ui} key while entering data in the
 @{"Radix Data Entry Window" LINK RadixWin} or in the
 @{"Transits Data Entry Window" LINK TransitsWin}, a little help window
 will pop up.

@ENDNODE

@node Windows "Usage - Windows"
@TOC Usage


   @{b}Windows@{ub}


   @{"Graphics Output Window    " LINK GfxWin}

   @{"Radix Data Entry Window   " LINK RadixWin}

   @{"Transits Data Entry Window" LINK TransitsWin}


   @{fg fill}NOTE:@{fg text}

   Use the @{b}depth gadget@{ub} to cycle through the windows overlayed on
 the right.

   Use the @{b}ESC@{ub} key to abort any data entry, thus re-enabling
 menus.

@ENDNODE


@NODE Project "Usage - Project Menu"
@TOC Usage


   @{b}Project Menu@{ub}


   This Menu gives the following possibilities:


   @{b}Enter Radix@{ub} : opens the @{"Radix Data Entry Window" LINK RadixWin}

   @{b}Load Radix@{ub}  : opens a requester to load birth data

                 @{fg shine}(registered version only)@{fg text}

   @{b}Save Radix@{ub}  : opens a requester to save birth data

                 @{fg shine}(registered version only)@{fg text}

   @{b}About...@{ub}    : about @{i}Neptune@{ui}

   @{b}Quit@{ub}        : quits the program.


   @{fg fill}NOTE:@{fg text}

   Neptune can load also Birth data in @{"Amiga ASTRO" LINK AstroPDL} format.

@endnode

@NODE Display "Usage - Display Menu"
@TOC Usage


   @{b}Display Menu@{ub}


   This Menu gives the following possibilities:


   @{b}R-R Pos@{ub} : displays positive aspects among @{"Radical" LINK Radical} planets (in blue)

   @{b}R-R Neg@{ub} : displays negative aspects among @{"Radical" LINK Radical} planets (in red)

   @{b}Glyphs@{ub}  : displays planets gliphs (=traditional symbols)

   @{b}Interpr@{ub} : displays a verbose list of planetary aspects and positions.

@endnode

@NODE Transits "Usage - Transits Menu"
@TOC Usage


   @{b}Transits Menu@{ub}


   This Menu gives the following possibilities:


   @{b}Entry@{ub}   : opens a @{"window" LINK TransitsWin} for keyboard

             input of transits (=non birth) data

   @{b}T-T Pos@{ub} : displays positive aspects among @{"Transient" LINK Trans} planets (in blue)

   @{b}T-T Neg@{ub} : displays negative aspects among @{"Transient" LINK Trans} planets (in red)

   @{b}R-T Pos@{ub} : displays positive aspects among @{"Radical" LINK Radical} and @{"Transient" LINK Trans}

             planets (in blue)

   @{b}R-T Neg@{ub} : displays negative aspects among @{"Radical" LINK Radical} and @{"Transient" LINK Trans}

             planets (in red).


   @{fg fill}NOTE:@{fg text}

   @{"Transient" LINK Trans} planets are always drawn in an inner circle, @{"Radical" LINK Radical} planets in an outer one.

@endnode

@NODE Print "Usage - Print Menu"
@TOC Usage


   @{b}Print Menu@{ub}


   This Menu gives the following possibilities @{fg shine}(only registered version)@{fg text}:


   @{b}Graphics@{ub} : sends the content of the graphic output window to the printer

   @{b}Text@{ub}     : prints planetary positions, aspects and houses values

   @{b}Both@{ub}     : both of the above.


   @{fg fill}NOTE:@{fg text}

   In order to obtain a printed image of the desidered size, you could wish
 to change your graphic printer options by double-clicking on @{b}PrinterGfx@{ub}
 in your @{b}SYS:Prefs@{ub} drawer. For example, to print a zodiac about 6
 inches wide, choose the following setting:


   Activate @{b}Center Picture@{ub} and set @{b}Limits@{ub} to:

   Type: @{fg shine}Absolute@{fg text}

   Width  (inches/10): @{fg shine}56@{fg text}

   Height (inches/10): @{fg shine}0@{fg text}

@endnode

@NODE Animate "Usage - Animate Menu"
@TOC Usage


   @{b}Animate Menu@{ub}


   This Menu gives the following possibilities:


   @{b}No@{ub}      : while drawing, planets appear already at their destinations

   @{b}Slowest@{ub} : planets move very slowly to their destinations

   @{b}Slow@{ub}    : planets move slowly to their destinations

   @{b}Medium@{ub}  : planets move at average speed to their destinations

   @{b}Fast@{ub}    : planets move fast to their destinations

   @{b}Fastest@{ub} : planets move very fast to their destinations.


   @{fg fill}NOTE:@{fg text}

   Animations have no practical use but to make the program look nicer.

@endnode


