@node GfxWin "Usage - Graphics Output Window"
@TOC Usage


   @{b}The Graphics Output Window@{ub}


   This window shows the graphic output of the various operations.

@endnode

@node RadixWin "Usage - Radix Data Entry Window"
@TOC Usage


   @{b}The Radix Data Entry Window@{ub}


   This window allows the input of the following data for the
 @{i}Radical Horoscope@{ui}, also called @{i}Natal Horoscope@{ui}
 or @{i}Birth Horoscope@{ui}:


   @{b}Name@{ub}        : the complete name of the subject,

                 which will be used as filename when data are saved

                 (eg. Stefano Baccara, which will produce

                 'Stefano_Baccara.HOR' as filename)

   @{b}Day@{ub}         : the day of birth

                 (eg. 26)

   @{b}Month@{ub}       : the month of birth

                 (eg. 12 for December)

   @{b}Year@{ub}        : the year of birth (between 1800 and 2099)

                 (eg. 1969)

   @{b}Time@{ub}        : the time of birth 

                 as shown by local watches at the instant of birth

                 (eg. 14.25 for 02.25 PM)

   @{b}City@{ub}        : the place of birth

                 (eg. Trieste)

   @{b}Long@{ub}        : the @{"Longitude" LINK Long} of the place of birth

                 (eg. +013.45 for 13°45'E, -013.45 for 13°45'W)

   @{b}Lat@{ub}         : the @{"Latitude" LINK Long} of the place of birth

                 (eg. +45.39 for 45°39'N, -45.39 for 45°39'S)

   @{b}TZ@{ub}          : the Time Zone, that is how many hours from the

                 Greenwich Medium Time (GMT)

                 (eg. 0 for GMT, -1 for one hour EAST from GMT,

                 +2 for two hours WEST)

   @{b}Summer Time@{ub} : Daylight-Saving Time

                 (eg. 0 for none, 1 for one hour)


   @{fg fill}NOTE:@{fg text}

   Use the @{i}Cursor keys@{ui} or the @{i}Tab key@{ui} to move through
 the different input fields.

   Press @{i}Ctrl-x@{ui} to delete the whole content of an input field.

   Press the @{i}Enter key@{ui} in the last field (Summer Time) to start
 the calculations.

   Use the @{i}Esc key@{ui} to abort any data entry, thus re-enabling menus.

@endnode

@node TransitsWin "Usage - Transits Data Entry Window"
@TOC Usage


   @{b}The Transits Data Entry Window@{ub}


   This window allows the input of the following data for the
 @{i}Transits Horoscope@{ui}, which compares the positions of the
 @{i}radical@{ui} with the @{i}transient@{ui} planets:


   @{b}Day@{ub}         : the day in exam

                 (eg. 26)

   @{b}Month@{ub}       : the month in exam

                 (eg. 12 for December)

   @{b}Year@{ub}        : the year in exam (between 1800 and 2099)

                 (eg. 1969)

   @{b}Time@{ub}        : the time in exam

                 (eg. 14.25 for 02.25 PM)

   @{b}TZ@{ub}          : the Time Zone in exam

                 (eg. 0 for GMT, -1 for one hour EAST from GMT,

                 +2 for two hours WEST)

   @{b}Summer Time@{ub} : Daylight-Saving Time of the moment in exam

                 (eg. 0 for none, 1 for one hour)

@endnode

