@node Astro "Neptune Documentation - The Basics of Astrology"


   @{b}The Basics of Astrology@{ub}


   If your knowledge of Astrology limits to the name of your sign, be aware
 that this old 'science' could offer you something more than what you can
 read in your newspaper's daily horoscope. Indeed one of the most powerful
 possibilities of Astrology is not so much the @{i}prediction@{ui} of
 future events (which might be achieved with the analisys of
 @{"transits" LINK Trans}), but a quite deep @{i}psychological analisys@{ui}
 of your personality.

   The principal instruments Astrology makes use of are:


   Planetary positions in Houses

   Planetary positions in Signs

   Aspects among Planets

   Houses' positions in Signs


   And for prediction:


   @{"Transient" LINK Trans} Planets' positions in Houses

   @{"Transient" LINK Trans} Planets' positions in Signs

   Aspects among @{"Transient" LINK Trans} and @{"Radical" LINK Radical} Planets


   The accurate analisys of these elements provides a huge amount of data,
 which can be joined to obtain a synthetic description of your psyche
 (highest accuracy), tendencies, tastes, background and soma, and in some
 cases to be able to - if not really predict - know with a certain degree
 of probability how a certain situation could develop.

@endnode

@node Trans "Neptune Documentation - Transits"


   @{b}Transits@{ub} are the positions of the planets of a certain date in
 the sky of your birth. Their analisys allows - with certain limits - to
 predict the future.

@endnode

@node Radical "Neptune Documentation - Radical"


   @{b}Radical@{ub} means relative to the instant of your birth.

@endnode

