@node Trouble "Neptune Documentation - Troubleshooting"


   @{b}Troubleshooting@{ub}


   @{fg shine}After clicking on its icon, Neptune does not start@{fg text}

   @{fg fill}Solution@{fg text}: make sure @{b}HBasic2.library@{ub}
 version 9.2 (1-June-1994) is in your LIBS: path.

   Make sure your @{b}OS@{ub} is at least @{b}2.04@{ub}.


   @{fg shine}After selecting any animation speed different than 'No' from
 the @{"Animate" LINK Animate} Menu, the screen gets trashed@{fg text}

   This problem may occur with some @{"graphic boards" LINK Gfxboard} and
 for the moment the only solution is to avoid the use of animations leaving
 the default @{b}No@{ub}.


   @{fg shine}It does not seem to be possible to LOAD, SAVE or PRINT anything!@{fg text}

   This is normal in the @{b}DEMO Version@{ub}.


   @{fg shine}Nothing seems to happen when 'T-T Pos' or 'T-T Neg' are selected
 from the @{"transits" LINK Transits} Menu@{fg text}

   This frequent phoenomenon derives from the fact that only @{b}very tight@{ub}
 aspects orbits are considered (as their influence in the analysis of
 Transits is notoriously low).


   @{fg shine}The program refuses to use my deafault fonts@{fg text}

   This may occur when your @{b}screen resolution@{ub} and @{b}overscan@{ub}
 - to which Neptune will adapt - are not sufficient to match with your
 deafult @{b}font size@{ub}. 

   @{fg fill}Solution@{fg text}: select a @{b}smaller default font size@{ub}
 or a @{b}higher screen resolution@{ub} and/or @{b}overscan@{ub} from the
 Preferences of the Workbench.


   @{fg shine}The fonts used by the program are not very intelligible,
 in particular there is no clear distinction between '1' and '4',
 and 'M' and 'N'@{fg text}

   This is caused by the fact that Neptune had to switch to the
 @{b}topaz 7@{ub} fonts because @{"nami fonts" LINK Nami} could not be found
 and your screen resolution and/or overscan were not adequate for other
 font sizes.

   @{fg fill}Solution@{fg text}: put @{"nami fonts" LINK Nami} in FONTS:


   @{fg shine}After launching Neptune, a requester pops up saying:

   @{b}Fonts not found!@{ub}@{fg text}

   Neither @{"nami fonts" LINK Nami} nor topaz fonts could be found in
 FONTS:

   @{fg fill}Solution@{fg text}: put topaz fonts or - better - @{"nami fonts" LINK Nami}
 in FONTS:


   @{fg shine}The program does not seem to work with my printer@{fg text}

   This problem could occur with some printers which are not yet entirely
 supported by their current drivers (eg. Canon BJC-150, which - at the moment
 this guide was written - does not work in TEXT MODE).

   @{fg fill}Solution@{fg text}: try to obtain an updated driver supporting
 100% your printer or - if not available - press 'W' to manually toggle
 between grey and white background and use GraphicDump (usually located in your
 WorkBench:Tools drawer) to print in graphic mode.


   @{fg shine}I don't know anything about Astrology!@{fg text}

   This can be more or less easily resolved reading some @{b}good books@{ub}
 about the subject. But caution needs to be taken in their choice because
 not many of them are really @{b}good@{ub}. An example of @{b}good@{ub}
 Author is Lisa Morpurgo.


@endnode

