@node rt "rt_RequestDevice"


   @{b}rt_RequestDevice@{ub} 37.3 (30.6.97) by @{"Nils Görs" LINK Nils}


   TITLE/K     = requestertitle.

   VAR/K       = name of the variable. If VAR is set the devicename will not
 be printed in shell. The variable type is global.

   LOCAL/S     = this switches the variable from global to local.

   PUBSCREEN/K = name of the public screen on which to open the device requester.

   DIRS/S      = opens the requester as directory requester.

   NOASSIGNS/S = opens the device requester without assigns.

   NODISKS/S   = opens the device requester without disks.


   rt_RequestDevice is reentrant.


@endnode

@node Bugs "Bugs"


   @{b}Bugs ?!!???!!@{ub}


   Should you have any trouble running Neptune, please @{"write me" LINK Author}
 with the full specifications of your machine.

   If you have suggestions or remarks about this program, or if you find
 any bug, please let me know.

   When sending bug reports, please state exactly under what circumstances
 the bug occurred, what equipment was used and what happened.


@endnode

@node Fee "Registration Fee"

   @{b}@{fg shine}IMPORTANT NOTE@{fg text}@{ub} To be able to receive the program
by @{b}EMail@{ub}, make sure your Mail Box supports @{fg fill}File Attachement@{fg text}!


   @{b}@{u}Registration Fee you have to pay in order to have the program sent to you by Mail/EMail@{uu}:


@{fg shine}                      EMail              Mail (Floppy Disk)@{ub}@{fg text}

Italian Lire          Lit  30.000.-      Lit 40.000.-

US Dollars            US$      20.-      US$     30.-

German Marks           DM      30.-       DM     40.-


   @{b}Payment types@{ub}


   @{fg fill}Cash@{fg text}

   This is the preferred payment since it is the cheapest and fastest.
 Simply put the banknotes in an envelope, making sure they are NOT visible
 looking through the envelope (for better safety you can wrap the banknotes
 in a sheet of paper).

   But consider two things:

      1.Never send coins!

      2.I will take no responsability if your money should get lost...


   @{fg fill}Eurocheque@{fg text}

   You can send an Eurocheque if you are living in Europe, but make sure
it is really an Eurocheque and not a private cheque.


   @{fg fill}National Cheque@{fg text}

   Use it only if you live in Italy. No additional cost.


   @{fg fill}Foreign Cheque@{fg text}

   If you want to use this very expensive type of payment, the registration
fee has to become:

@{fg shine}                      EMail              Mail (Floppy Disk)@{ub}@{fg text}

Italian Lire          Lit  40.000.-      Lit 50.000.-

US Dollars            US$      30.-      US$     40.-

German Marks           DM      40.-       DM     50.-


   @{fg fill}Postal Money Order (PMO)@{fg text}

   If you choose this labor-intensive payment method, you have to visit
your local post office and place a PMO by paying in your own currency.

@endnode
